# Contributing to {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Development Workflow

This project uses the [claude-workflow](https://github.com/{{WORKFLOW_REPO}}) AI-assisted development workflow.

### Lifecycle

```
/draft → /plan → /implement → /pr → /release
```

1. **Draft** — Add raw ideas to backlog: `/draft feature "idea"`
2. **Refine** — Turn a draft into a ready spec in one light pass: `/plan FEAT-001`
3. **Implement** — Write tests first, then code: `/implement FEAT-001`
4. **PR** — CI runs, then AI reviews, then auto-merge: `/pr`
5. **Release** — Version bump + tag + publish: `/release patch`

### Branch Naming
```
feature/feat-001-short-title
fix/bug-042-short-description
chore/update-dependencies
```

### Branching & Pushing Rules
- **Push to your feature branch freely** — after every commit is fine. Pushes are backups, not quality statements.
- **The quality gate sits at the merge**: merging into the integration branch happens only via `/pr` (CI green, AI code/security review findings fixed).
- **Never push directly to the integration branch** (`develop` in git flow, otherwise `main`). Exception: `/release` performs the release merge into `master` (git flow).
- **Git flow projects**: `master` contains only released states — its tip always equals the latest release tag.

### Commit Format
Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):
```
feat(auth): add OAuth login with Google
fix(session): correct token expiry calculation
test(auth): add OAuth integration tests
docs(api): update authentication endpoints
chore: update dependencies
```

Types: `feat` | `fix` | `refactor` | `test` | `docs` | `chore` | `perf` | `ci`

### Definition of Ready (before implementation)
- [ ] User Story is clear (who / what / why)
- [ ] All acceptance criteria are testable
- [ ] Interface definitions are complete
- [ ] All subtasks defined
- [ ] No open questions
- [ ] RE sign-off + TP sign-off

### Definition of Done (before merge)
- [ ] All tests pass (CI green)
- [ ] Linter clean
- [ ] All code review findings addressed
- [ ] All security review findings addressed
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Spec moved to `docs/specs/completed/`

